    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Once the onion has softened, increase the heat to medium-high and add your <strong>beef mince </strong>with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[275ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pod[s]</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife</p><p>Once the beef mince has browned, add the <strong>crushed cardamom pod[s]</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cinnamon</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>allspice</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomatoes begin to break down</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained green lentils</strong>,<strong> tomato stock </strong>and<strong> </strong>a generous pinch<strong> </strong>of<strong> salt</strong> to the pan with the beef mince and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-18 min or until thickened and the beef mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your warming <strong>Persian-style beef & lentil stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the stew is cooking, wash your <strong>spinach</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> spinach</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 1-2 min or until the spinach is wilted</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-persian-style-beef-and-lentil-stew-with-feta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>warming Persian-style beef & lentil stew</strong> next to the<strong> cooked rice</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for any cardamom pods!</p><p>Crumble your <strong>feta</strong> over the top and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
